<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F, 3/2 (three half-note beats per measure). "33" root triads.
- B° (non-diatonic in bar 2) → elided, treat as passing motion within F → C.
- =B (natural Bb) in bars 2 and 6 is a melodic inflection; harp stays on Bb diatonic.
- LH: full open F triad root-pos on every F change. Variety through inversions at bar 7-8.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Half-note harmonic rhythm suits the broad 3/2 feel.
- Bar 8 three-chord cadence Bb-C-F spells out the full authentic cadence.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Stately 3/2 feel throughout. Builds bar 6 (high G5 RH). Final bar 9: dotted whole cadence.
-->
